post_text: Thank you to everyone who came out last night to help support Nancy Drake and her family. Thanks to your generous donations from both the Benton and Murphysboro communities, we were able to raise a total of $1,000 for this family. We may be divided on the court, but we are united in the fight against cancer. If you would like to order one of the Cancer Game shirts, there is a link in the comments or email Victoria Jackson at vjackson@bentonhighschool.org

Tuesday, September 25th we will be hosting a Cancer Game. We will be raffling off these 5 baskets to help raise money for a local family battling cancer. The freshmen will begin at 5:15pm, JV at 6:15pm and Varsity at 7:15pm. Before the varsity game, we will draw for winners of the baskets and have a special presentation to the family. We hope to see you there as we “dig for a cure”.

post_text: We are going to practice July 5, 6, 7, 11, 12, 13, 18, 19, 20, 24, 25, 26, 27, and 28 from 9-11am. Then we will break for "dead week." Coach Carlton will post the team at the end of the summer (date TBA). We will start back on August 10 . If you can't make it to some of the dates, let Coach know. We have some tourney dates throughout the summer, but will not be taking everyone. We will let you know as those dates approach if you have been selected to go. If you aren't selected to attend the tournament, you will have practice from 9-11 on those dates. Also, if you know any one else who is interested in playing, please forward this message. Thanks, see you Wednesday!

post_text:
Directions to Potter's Way Church for the banquet tomorrow:
Leaving Benton and going North on 37, turn right at Burtons. Go past Ewing and keeping driving (for about 5-10 miles possibly?) turn left onto Frisco Rd at the church sign. Follow the road and the church will be on the right.
If you are driving on Hwy 14 coming out of Benton, drive for 8-9 miles turn left onto camp hope rd. Go all the way down and turn right onto ewing blacktop then turn left onto frisco road at the church sign.
17162 Frisco Rd. Ewing Il 62836

Benton Rangerette Volleyball
September 19, 2016 at 8:34 PM ·

It was a great weekend for Rangerette Volleyball. Our freshmen took1st place at the Salem tourney and our JV Team took third at the Fairfield tourney. Tomorrow we will play Harrisburg at home with the freshmen beginning at 5:30pm.

Amy Calcaterra and Ginger Reno have the first shift of concessions beginning at 5:15pm and Deb Keelin and Amy Tabor have the second shift beginning at 6:45pm.

Thursday we travel to Massac with our bus leaving at 3:45pm.

Benton Rangerette Volleyball
September 10, 2016 at 8:07 PM ·

Congrats to Woodlawn on winning the Rangerette Classic. The Benton Rangerettes took second. Valmeyer won the Silver division and Pinckneyville won the Bronze division. Congratulations to all the girls who made the All Tournament Team (especially our own). Thank you to all the parents and players who worked, everyone who donated anything, all the fans for coming, and the Pedigo family for running our concessions. It was another successful year.
